  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients treated with first line chemotherapy with intravenous (IV) to solid tumors or
        hematologic.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Aged over 18 years

          -  With solid tumors or hematologic in first line chemotherapy, administered
             intravenously,

          -  Able to understand the meaning of the questions

          -  Having given their written consent to participate in the survey.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        This does not concern patients who:

          -  Do not give their consent for participation

          -  Do not speak French

          -  Suffer from cognitive deficits

          -  Are under therapy

          -  Must receive a combination of radio-chemotherapy

          -  Present an occlusive syndrome

          -  Metastases (s) brain (s) clinically symptomatic (s) or radiologically proven (s) or a
             (of) tumor (s) brain (s)

          -  Have been previously treated with chemotherapy

          -  Present a cons-indication to corticosteroids, with anti-serotonin or NK1 receptor
             inhibitors

          -  Pregnant or breastfeeding.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
